- The `findLongestCommonSubstring` method takes two strings as input and returns the longest common substring between them using dynamic programming.
    - An integer array `lengths` is used to store the lengths of longest common substrings for each prefix of `str1` and `str2`.
    - The two outer loops iterate over each character of `str1` and `str2`, and if the current characters match, the corresponding entry in `lengths` is updated by adding 1 to the length of the longest common substring of the previous prefixes.
    - The `maxLength` variable stores the length of the longest common substring found so far, and `endIndex` stores the index of the end of this substring in `str1`.
- The main method calls `findLongestCommonSubstring` and prints the result to the console depending on whether a common substring was found or not.

